State Championship of Rio de Janeiro 1985

1985 RIO DE JANEIRO STATE CHAMPIONSHIP                               

Participants

América (Rio de Janeiro)
Americano (Campos)
Bangu (Rio de Janeiro)
Bonsucesso (Rio de Janeiro)
Botafogo (Rio de Janeiro)
Flamengo (Rio de Janeiro)
Fluminense (Rio de Janeiro)
Goytacaz (Campos)
Olaria (Rio de Janeiro)
Portuguesa (Rio de Janeiro)
Vasco (Rio de Janeiro)
Volta Redonda (Volta Redonda)

The tournament was divided into 2 stages, stage winners qualified to the 
final playoff.  If the team with the better season record does not win a 
stage, that team also qualified to the final playoff.


First Stage - Taça Guanabara

